cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new flavor of Variational Autoencoder (VAE) that can seamlessly interpolate between unsupervised, semi-supervised, and fully supervised learning domains. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given that the paper focuses on VAEs and their applications to classification tasks, we believe that cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.NE.
